You are building IronIQ - an AI-powered gym management and coaching platform for India (Tier 2/3 cities).

Stack: Next.js 14 App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, Supabase, Claude API, Razorpay, Vercel.

Architecture Rules:
- All Supabase and Claude API calls go in /app/api/ route handlers ONLY. Never call them from client components directly.
- Use server components by default. Add "use client" only when needed for interactivity.
- Database logic in /lib/db/. UI logic in /components/. Business logic in /lib/services/.
- Each feature gets its own folder under /features/

Design System:
- Background: #07090F (near black)
- Primary accent: #0ECFB0 (cyan-green)
- Secondary: #1A2332 (dark navy)
- Text primary: #F1F5F9
- Text muted: #94A3B8
- Font: Inter for body, Syne for headings
- Dark theme ONLY. Mobile-first. Every component works at 375px.
- No Lorem Ipsum. Use realistic Indian gym context in all placeholder text.
- Names: Rahul, Priya, Arjun, Sneha. Cities: Dharwad, Nagpur, Hubli, Belgaum.

India Rules:
- All prices in ₹ INR
- Phone: +91 format
- Payments: Razorpay UPI/card
- Language: English UI with Hinglish flavor in copy ("Bhai", "Kal", "Aaj")
- Food: Indian meals only (dal, roti, paneer, eggs)

AI Rules:
- Always pass gym equipment list as context when generating workout plans
- Always include user level (beginner/intermediate/advanced) in every AI call
- Voice output in Hinglish: natural mix of Hindi words
- Never generate exercises using equipment not in the gym inventory
